This paper deals with differentially private empirical risk minimization, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the geometry of the constraint set, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for optimization, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
